I have the edit plan. I’m replacing the current verifier with a simpler version that keeps the same exploit causality but makes the two abuse branches structurally explicit: `selfSwap` with `tokenOut.amount = 0`, then `router.call(routerData)` against an ERC20, using either `transfer(...)` for Dexible-held balances or `transferFrom(...)` when a victim is known.
